    think='Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me start imp
lementing the profile feature systematically. Given the complexity, I\'ll use su
bagents where appropriate to parallelize work, but since many pieces depend on e
ach other, I\'ll do a lot directly.\n\nLet me plan the implementation:\n\n1. **B
ackend - Auth Module Fix**: Export TypeOrmModule so ProfileModule can reuse enti
ties\n2. **Backend - Profile Module**: Create profile controller, service, DTOs\
n3. **Backend - Photo Module**: Create photo controller, service, DTOs  \n4. **B
ackend - OSS Module**: Create OSS presigned URL controller and service\n5. **Bac
kend - ProfileCompletionGuard**: Guard that checks is_complete\n6. **Backend - A
ppModule**: Register new modules\n7. **Backend - API Contract**: Update profile.
yaml\n8. **Mobile - Profile Repository**: Abstract and implementation\n9. **Mobi
le - Profile BLoC**: States, events, bloc\n10. **Mobile - Profile Setup Page**: 
Step-by-step UI\n11. **Mobile - Profile Edit Page**: Edit UI with photo grid\n12
. **Mobile - Design System**: SwPhotoGrid, SwPhotoCard, SwBottomSheet\n13. **Mob
ile - Widgetbook**: Register new components\n14. **Mobile - Routes**: Update app
.dart routes\n15. **Mobile - DI**: Update di.dart\n16. **Tests - BDD**: Step def
initions\n17. **Docs**: Update INDEX.md and AGENTS.md if needed\n\nLet me start 
with the backend modules. I\'ll use the auth module\'s entities since they corre
ctly map to the DB schema.\n\nActually, I realize there\'s an issue - the auth m
odule uses `UserProfileEntity` with properties like `isComplete`, `userId`, `ava
tarUrl`, `birthDate`, `preferredGender`, `preferredMinAge`, `preferredMaxAge`, `
photoUrls`. But the PRD and the `database/entities/user-profile.entity.ts` use `
is_complete`, `preferred_gender`, `age_range_min`, `age_range_max` (not preferre
d_min_age).\n\nLet me check the migration again carefully:\n- `preferred_gender 
VARCHAR(20) NULL`\n- `preferred_min_age INT NULL`\n- `preferred_max_age INT NULL
`\n\nOK so the migration uses `preferred_min_age` and `preferred_max_age`, which
matches the auth entity\'s `preferredMinAge` and `preferredMaxAge` (with `name:`
mapping).\n\nBut the PRD says `preferred_age_min` and `preferred_age_max` in the
DTOs. And the existing profile.yaml contract says `age_range_min` and `age_range
_max`.\n\nWait, looking at the existing profile.yaml contract:\n```yaml\nage_ran
ge_min:\n  type: integer\nage_range_max:\n  type: integer\n```\n\nBut the DB sch
ema from migration has `preferred_min_age` and `preferred_max_age`. The auth ent
ity maps `preferredMinAge` → `preferred_min_age`.\n\nThere\'s a naming mismatch 
between the contract (age_range_min) and the DB (preferred_min_age). I should pr
obably update the contract to match the DB, or add both fields to the entity. Bu
t since I can\'t modify the DB schema easily (it would require a migration), and
the existing auth entity maps to `preferred_min_age`, I\'ll use `preferred_min_a
ge` in the backend but expose it as `age_range_min` in the DTO/response for API 
consistency with the existing contract.\n\nWait, actually looking more carefully
at the auth entity:\n```typescript\n@Column("int", { nullable: true, name: "pref
erred_min_age" })\npreferredMinAge: number | null;\n\n@Column("int", { nullable:
true, name: "preferred_max_age" })\npreferredMaxAge: number | null;\n```\n\nAnd 
the PRD says:\n- `preferred_age_min` / `preferred_age_max`: integer, range 18-80
\n\nBut the existing profile.yaml says `age_range_min` / `age_range_max`.\n\nThe
plan\'s Step 1 says:\n```typescript\ncreate-profile.dto.ts（`nickname`, `gender`
, `birth_date`, `latitude`, `longitude`, `bio?`, `tags?`, `preferred_gender?`, `
preferred_age_min?`, `preferred_age_max?`）\n```\n\nSo the plan uses `preferred_
age_min` / `preferred_age_max` in DTOs. The existing contract uses `age_range_mi
n` / `age_range_max`.\n\nI think the safest approach is:\n1. Update the API cont
ract to use `preferred_age_min` and `preferred_age_max` to match the plan and PR
D\n2. In the backend, map these DTO fields to `preferredMinAge` / `preferredMaxA
ge` in the entity\n\nWait, but the mobile generated models are already based on 
the existing profile.yaml contract. If I change the contract, the generated mode
ls would need to be regenerated. Let me check what fields the generated models u
se.',
