    think='Now I see the issue clearly. The migrations are loaded by glob patter
n `join(__dirname, "./migrations/*{.ts,.js}")`. Both migrations have the same ti
mestamp prefix `20250410000000`. The order depends on filesystem ordering, but t
ypically `InitialSchema` comes before `CreateUsersAndUserProfiles` alphabeticall
y.\n\nSo the actual DB schema is from `InitialSchema`, which means:\n- `user_pro
files`: `user_id` is PRIMARY KEY, no `id`, no `avatar_url`, `age_range_min`/`age
_range_max`\n- `user_photos`: exists with the correct schema\n\nBut the auth mod
ule\'s entity is completely wrong for this schema. It has `id` as PK and maps to
columns that don\'t exist (`preferred_min_age`, `avatar_url`).\n\nHOWEVER, looki
