/modules/**/*.entity{.ts,.js}`. The auth entity is at `apps/api/src/modules/auth
/entities/user-profile.entity.ts`. Since the auth module imports this entity int
o `TypeOrmModule.forFeature()`, TypeORM will try to use it.\n\nWait, but if the 
entity doesn\'t match the DB schema, how does the auth service work? When `findO
rCreateUser` calls `this.profileRepo.create({ id: profileId, userId, isComplete:
false })` and then `save()`, it would try to insert into a table with `id` colum
n which doesn\'t exist.\n\nUnless... `synchronize: false` means TypeORM doesn\'t
modify the schema, but it still tries to execute SQL based on the entity. The in
sert would fail with "Unknown column \'id\'".\n\nThis suggests the existing code
base may not actually run properly. But I need to make it work for this issue.\n
\nThe pragmatic fix: I should update the auth module\'s `UserProfileEntity` to m
atch the ACTUAL DB schema from `InitialSchema`. This is the root cause of the in
