ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think="Now I see the problem! The `AdminModule` uses `database/entities` whi
ch have `user_id` as primary key in `UserProfileEntity`, but the auth module use
s its own entities with `id` as primary key. The migration shows `id` is the pri
mary key. This means the admin module's entity is WRONG and would fail if actual
ly used.\n\nThe auth module's entity is correct according to the migration. Sinc
e `autoLoadEntities: true` loads ALL entities from ALL TypeOrmModule.forFeature(
) calls, having both auth entities and admin entities for the same table would c
ause conflicts.\n\nWait, actually `autoLoadEntities: true` only auto-loads entit
ies that are registered in `TypeOrmModule.forFeature()`. Both AuthModule and Adm
inModule register UserProfileEntity. If they map to the same table with differen
t column definitions, TypeORM might have issues.\n\nLet me check if the admin se
rvice actually works with the wrong entity definition.",
    encrypted=None
)
