1/profile` for the basic profile operations, and add new endpoints under it or u
nder separate controllers. The PRD's `/users/me/profile` is just a naming conven
tion - the actual contract has already been established as `/api/v1/profile`.\n\
nFor the photo and OSS endpoints, I'll add them as new paths in the contract and
implement corresponding controllers. Let me check what path prefix is standard i
n this project. Looking at auth: `/api/v1/auth/login`, `/api/v1/auth/me`. So the
controllers use relative paths without `/api/v1`.\n\nFor profile, I'll use:\n- `
GET /api/v1/profile` - get profile\n- `POST /api/v1/profile` - create/update pro
file (for setup)\n- `PATCH /api/v1/profile` - partial update profile (for edit)\
n\nWait, but the existing generated code only has POST, not PATCH. And the mobil
e `DefaultApi` only has `updateProfile` which sends POST. I could either:\n1. Ch
ange the existing contract to add PATCH and regenerate\n2. Use POST for both cre
ate and update (which is what the existing code does)\n\nThe PRD says:\n- `POST 
/users/me/profile` - first create\n- `PATCH /users/me/profile` - edit\n\nBut the
existing contract only has POST. For simplicity and to avoid regenerating models
, I'll make the POST endpoint handle both create and full update (as it already 
does), and I'll add a PATCH endpoint for partial updates. The mobile can use Dio
directly for PATCH if needed, or we can just use POST for everything.\n\nActuall
y, looking at the PRD more carefully, it says the BDD tests expect `PATCH /users
